        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 1:48PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 148 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Canton, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Canton, Jasper, Kennesaw, Woodstock, Acworth, Holly Springs, Ball
Ground, Nelson, Waleska, Free Home, Buffington, Hickory Flat, Kellogg
Creek, Red Top Mountain State Park, Lathemtown, Tate, Hobgood Park,
Union Hill, Lake Arrowhead, and Marblehill.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
